<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF2682F459A311EBFFAFBDE" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF2682F459A311EBFFAFBDE" blockId="7.[151,1437,901,1755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F459A311EBB39FBA2" bold="true" box="[199,322,1045,1071]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF2682F4480311EB8B7FBA2" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[477,716,1045,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Wellsomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamoides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F4480311EB8B7FBA2" box="[477,716,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Wellsomina tamoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F4789311EB94BFBA2" bold="true" box="[724,816,1045,1071]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFF2682F4789311EB94BFBA2" box="[724,816,1045,1071]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF2682F415E311DBF68FBA2" authority="Cartwright 2010" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2010" box="[1027,1299,1045,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Wellsomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tam">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F415E311DBE2AFBA2" box="[1027,1105,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">W. tam</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF2682F4107311EBF68FBA2" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[1114,1299,1045,1071]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref14689" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2010) Descriptions of 2 new genera and 13 new species of caddisflies from Australia (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 2415 (1), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2415.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Cartwright 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from North 
<collectingRegion id="499AEFCEFFF2682F45CA3132BB60FBDE" box="[151,283,1081,1107]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Queensland</collectingRegion>
in all genitalic structures but can be separated by the slenderer branches of the superior appendages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF2682F459A3156BBE4F9E2" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF2682F459A3156B875FAA6" blockId="7.[151,1437,901,1755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F459A3156BBE2FBFA" bold="true" box="[199,409,1117,1143]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Description, male</emphasis>
. Spur formula: 3:4:4. Head, body light brown, abdomen paler ventrally and wings damaged, grey-brownish, wings similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF2682F47023189B8B1FB16" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2010" box="[607,714,1154,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Wellsomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stuarti">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F47023189B8B1FB16" box="[607,714,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">W. stuarti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF2682F478A318AB9EFFB16" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[727,916,1153,1179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref14689" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2010) Descriptions of 2 new genera and 13 new species of caddisflies from Australia (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 2415 (1), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2415.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Cartwright 2010</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 7), length of each forewing: male 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFF2682F401C318ABFE2FB11" box="[1345,1433,1153,1180]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="290" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Wing venation: forewings each with forks 2, 3, 4, and 5 present; fork 2 relatively short, fork 2 footstalk relatively very long, length about 1.5 times length of cross-vein 
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F47A531C1B95BFB6E" box="[760,800,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">r -m</emphasis>
, length of fork 2 about 1.8 times length of fork 3; fork 3 short, length of fork 3 about same as length of footstalk, footstalk of fork 3 long. Hind wings each with forks 2, 3, and 5 present, all relatively short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF2682F459A303EBB8FF9C6" blockId="7.[151,1437,901,1755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F459A303EBB7AFAC2" box="[199,257,1333,1359]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Male</emphasis>
(Genitalia of illustrated 
<typeStatus id="54E59F8EFFF2682F4740303EB804FAC2" box="[541,639,1333,1359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">holotype</typeStatus>
male slightly damaged on right side). Tergum X membranous with 2 lobes (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F45BC3052BB48FAFE" box="[225,307,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), and ventrally directed intermediate process forming large apical spine (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F413F3052BECFFAFE" box="[1122,1204,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
, partly hidden in lateral views by ventral branches of superior appendages). Superior appendages branched, each with two semi-equal branches, inner dorsal branch with few apical spines on mesal lobe and single long spine on the outer lobe, outer ventral branch with three robust, spine-like setae apically (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F467830CEB9D3FA52" box="[805,936,1477,1503]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Figs 10–12</figureCitation>
). Phallus simple, tube-like (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F418230CEBF48FA52" box="[1247,1331,1477,1503]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages dorsoventrally depressed (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F471930E2B8BAF98E" box="[580,705,1513,1539]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Figs 10, 11</figureCitation>
), in ventral view fused in basal half, with pair of robust digitiform processes apically, separated widely in distal half by mesal split (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F46283306B9BCF9AA" box="[885,967,1549,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); in lateral view slender, tapering slightly and upturned distally (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFF2682F44CE333ABB9DF9C6" box="[403,486,1585,1611]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[362,1223,356,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-132@6.[352,1235,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–12. Ecnomidae. Figures 6–9, Neboissomina topendica sp. nov.: 6, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 7–9, male genitalia: 7, left lateral; 8, ventral; 9, dorsal. Figures 10–12, Wellsomina tamoides sp. nov. male genitalia: 10, left lateral; 11, ventral; 12, dorsal.Abbreviations: F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; ap. sp. X = apical spine tergum X; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); mes. pro. terg. X = mesal process tergum X (paired); pha. = phallus; sup. app. = superior appendage (paired); sup. app. dors. = dorsal branch of superior appendage (paired); sup. app. vent. = ventral branch of superior appendage (paired)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559743/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF2682F459A335EBBE4F9E2" blockId="7.[151,1437,901,1755]" box="[199,415,1621,1647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF2682F459A335EBB58F9E2" box="[199,291,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="290">Female.</emphasis>
